  "description": "The third and final edition of <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/reach-for-the-stars-the-conquest-of-the-galaxy\">Reach for the Stars: The Conquest of the Galaxy</a> is a near total rewrite of the game, replacing the entire structure and flow of the original with a menu-based interface similar to SSG's other games available in 1988, and for the first time is available on 16-bit platforms as well as the Apple II and Commodore 64 that <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/developer/sheet/view/developerId,14868/\">Roger Keating</a> and <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?developer=Ian+Trout\">Ian Trout</a> originally wrote it for.<br><br>In addition to the revamped interface and tweaks to the basic game, <i>RFTS 3.0</i> offers a new advanced scenario, with significant changes and additions, including ground armies, new mechanics on governing conquered planets, new technology trees for navigation and industrial capacity, and progressive social maintenance costs.",
